{"page_id": 8913, "slug": "Neon_Genesis_Evangelion:_Second_Impression", "title": "Neon Genesis Evangelion: Second Impression", "display_title": "<span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">Neon Genesis Evangelion: Second Impression</span>", "namespace": 0, "content_model": "wikitext", "language": null, "wikitext": "'''Second Impression''' (aka 2nd Impression) is a 1997 video game for the Sega Saturn. The plot features a new student in [[Shinji Ikari|Shinji's]] class, [[Extracanonical_Characters#Mayumi_Yamagishi|Mayumi Yamagishi]], a bookworm and good student, and Shinji's attempts to overcome his shyness and become her friend. The gameplay allows you to choose what to say to Mayumi and other students, sing karaoke (two original songs are included in the game), and whatnot. A new angel, meanwhile, the [[Extracanonical_Mecha#Insubstantial_Angel|Insubstantial Angel]], attacks Tokyo-3. It turns out that, somehow, the core of the angel is *inside* Mayumi, who attempts to commit suicide in the game's final scene.\n\nThe character design of [[Mari]], the new character in [[Evangelion 2.0|Rebuild 2.0]], resembles Mayumi insofar as they are both brunettes with glasses. \n\n==Merchandise==\n\nThe Saturn game came with an extra mini-cd containing the two theme song tracks, \"Get it on! To kiss a Doppelganger\" (sung by [[Asuka Langley Soryu|Asuka]]) and \"You are your own reason\" (sung by Mayumi). A book, ''2nd Impression Bible'', was published by Newtype and features screenshots, commentary by the production staff, sheet music to the new songs, etc.\n\n==Production==\n\nDirector & Storyboards: 村山靖 (? Osamu Murayama? )<br>\nWriter: Hiroshi Yamaguchi (scripted Eva episode 16 along with Anno)<br>\nIllustration Director: 大塚健 (Ken Ohtsuka?)<br>\nGuest character design: 高木弘樹 (Hiroki Takagi? No information on this guy) - presumably designed [[Extracanonical_Characters#Mayumi_Yamagishi|Mayumi]]?<br>\nGuest mecha design: Mahiro Maeda - presumably designed the [[Extracanonical_Mecha#Insubstantial_Angel|Insubstantial Angel]].<Br>\nAnimation: [http://www.pro-reed.com/ Production Reed Co.]<br>\n\n==Gallery==\n{{MontageBoxCollapse\n|float   = none\n|columns = 5\n|title   = Eva 2nd Impression images\n|image1  = [[Image:2ndimpression1.jpg|200px]]\n|image2  = [[Image:2ndimpression2.jpg|200px]]\n|image3  = [[Image:2ndimpression3.jpg|200px]]\n|image4  = [[Image:2ndimpression4.jpg|200px]]\n|image5  = [[Image:2ndimpression5.jpg|200px]]\n|image6  = [[Image:2ndimpression6.jpg|200px]]\n|image7  = [[Image:2ndimpression7.jpg|200px]]\n|image8  = [[Image:2ndimpression8.jpg|200px]]\n|image9  = [[Image:2ndimpression9.jpg|200px]]\n|image10 = [[Image:2ndimpression10.jpg|200px]]\n|image11 = [[Image:2ndimpression11.jpg|200px]]\n|image12  = [[Image:2ndimpression12.jpg|200px]]\n|image13  = [[Image:2ndimpression13.jpg|200px]]\n|image14  = [[Image:2ndimpression14.jpg|200px]]\n|image15  = [[Image:2ndimpression15.jpg|200px]]\n|image16  = [[Image:2ndimpression16.png|200px]]\n|image17  = [[Image:2ndimpression17.png |200px]]\n|image18  = [[Image:2ndimpression18.png |200px]]\n|image19  = [[Image:2ndimpression19.png|200px]]\n|image20  = [[Image:2ndimpression20.png|200px]]\n|image21  = [[Image:2ndimpression21.png|200px]]\n|image22  = [[Image:2ndimpression22.png|200px]]\n|image23  = [[Image:2ndimpression23.png|200px]]\n|image24  = [[Image:2ndimpression24.png|200px]]\n|image25  = [[Image:2ndimpression25.png|200px]]\n|image26  = [[Image:2ndimpression26.png|200px]]\n|image27  = [[Image:2ndimpression27.png|200px]]\n|image28  = [[Image:2ndimpression28.png|200px]]\n|image29  = [[Image:2ndimpression29.png|200px]]\n|image30  = [[Image:2ndimpression30.png|200px]]\n|image31  = [[Image:2ndimpression31.png|200px]]\n|image32  = [[Image:2ndimpression32.png|200px]]\n|image33  = [[Image:2ndimpression33.png|200px]]\n|image34  = [[Image:2ndimpression34.png|200px]]\n|image35  = [[Image:2ndimpression35.png|200px]]\n|image36  = [[Image:2ndimpression36.png|200px]]\n|image37  = [[Image:2ndimpression37.png|200px]]\n|caption =\n}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/新世紀エヴァンゲリオン_2nd_Impression Wikipedia Japan entry], via [http://www.google.com/translate?u=http%3A%2F%2Fja.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2F新世紀エヴァンゲリオン_2nd_Impression&hl=en&ie=UTF8&sl=ja&sl=es&tl=en&tl=en Google translation]\n*[http://www.ex.org/2.8/37-game_eva.html Ex.org review] - with screenshots.\n*[http://cheats.ign.com/ob2/068/002/002233.html IGN Walkthrough]\n*[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vpz6GEXUspk Opening animation] - online at Youtube.\n\n\n{{Video Games}}\n[[Category:A to Z]]\n[[Category:Video Games]]", "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Second Impression</b> (aka 2nd Impression) is a 1997 video game for the Sega Saturn. The plot features a new student in <a href=\"/Shinji_Ikari\" title=\"Shinji Ikari\">Shinji's</a> class, <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Characters#Mayumi_Yamagishi\" title=\"Extracanonical Characters\">Mayumi Yamagishi</a>, a bookworm and good student, and Shinji's attempts to overcome his shyness and become her friend. The gameplay allows you to choose what to say to Mayumi and other students, sing karaoke (two original songs are included in the game), and whatnot. A new angel, meanwhile, the <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Mecha#Insubstantial_Angel\" title=\"Extracanonical Mecha\">Insubstantial Angel</a>, attacks Tokyo-3. It turns out that, somehow, the core of the angel is *inside* Mayumi, who attempts to commit suicide in the game's final scene.\n</p><p>The character design of <a href=\"/Mari\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mari\">Mari</a>, the new character in <a href=\"/Evangelion_2.0\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Evangelion 2.0\">Rebuild 2.0</a>, resembles Mayumi insofar as they are both brunettes with glasses. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Merchandise\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Merchandise</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Production\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Production</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Gallery\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Gallery</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Merchandise\">Merchandise</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Neon_Genesis_Evangelion:_Second_Impression&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Merchandise\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The Saturn game came with an extra mini-cd containing the two theme song tracks, \"Get it on! To kiss a Doppelganger\" (sung by <a href=\"/Asuka_Langley_Soryu\" title=\"Asuka Langley Soryu\">Asuka</a>) and \"You are your own reason\" (sung by Mayumi). A book, <i>2nd Impression Bible</i>, was published by Newtype and features screenshots, commentary by the production staff, sheet music to the new songs, etc.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Production\">Production</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Neon_Genesis_Evangelion:_Second_Impression&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Production\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Director &amp; Storyboards: 村山靖 (? Osamu Murayama? )<br />\nWriter: Hiroshi Yamaguchi (scripted Eva episode 16 along with Anno)<br />\nIllustration Director: 大塚健 (Ken Ohtsuka?)<br />\nGuest character design: 高木弘樹 (Hiroki Takagi? No information on this guy) - presumably designed <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Characters#Mayumi_Yamagishi\" title=\"Extracanonical Characters\">Mayumi</a>?<br />\nGuest mecha design: Mahiro Maeda - presumably designed the <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Mecha#Insubstantial_Angel\" title=\"Extracanonical Mecha\">Insubstantial Angel</a>.<br />\nAnimation: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.pro-reed.com/\">Production Reed Co.</a><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Gallery\">Gallery</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Neon_Genesis_Evangelion:_Second_Impression&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Gallery\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<table align=\"center\" style=\"float: none; clear: none; ; text-align: center; vertical-align: center; font-size: 90%; background-color: white; border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; margin: 1em;\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\" border=\"0\" class=\"mw-collapsible mw-collapsed\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th style=\"background: tan; font-size: 120%;\" colspan=\"5\"><b>Eva 2nd Impression images</b>\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/File:2ndimpression1.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/2ndimpression1.jpg/200px-2ndimpression1.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"179\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/2ndimpression1.jpg/300px-2ndimpression1.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/2ndimpression1.jpg/400px-2ndimpression1.jpg 2x\" /></a></span></td>\n<td><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/File:2ndimpression2.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/2/2f/2ndimpression2.jpg/200px-2ndimpression2.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"179\" class=\"mw-file-element\" src